  <preparation>Trim flaps and membrane from ribs.   Mix together rub ingredients and reserve 2 Tbl for table preparation.  Coat ribs with rub at least an hour before cooking.  Combine cider and vinegar and warm to simmering.  

Cook ribs over indirect, smoky low heat for 3-4 hours, mopping every 30 minutes after the first hour.

Sprinkle 1 Tbl of rub over ribs while on the grill before removing and heat each side for an additional 30 seconds.

While meat cools, add remaining 1 Tbl of spice rub to the mop and reduce to 2 cups.  Season with hot sauce and serve.</preparation>
